00:35:00,840 --> 00:35:03,490
Drive! Drive!
沖 衝啊

555
00:35:03,950 --> 00:35:05,990
- Jesus, are you okay? - Yeah, I'm fine.
- 天 你還好嗎 - 沒事

556
00:35:06,010 --> 00:35:07,010
Move!
快點

557
00:35:07,610 --> 00:35:09,140
Spirit here, boys. Move!
都精神點 小伙子們 動作快

558
00:35:09,170 --> 00:35:10,480
Come on. Move!
加油 快跑

559
00:35:10,620 --> 00:35:11,810
What the hell is wrong with you?
你們在幹嘛呢

560
00:35:11,830 --> 00:35:13,610
No one said take a rest!
沒人說可以休息

561
00:35:13,640 --> 00:35:17,360
Move your asses to the finish line. Move! Move!
快給我跑到終點線去 快 快

562
00:35:18,100 --> 00:35:19,530
Hustle! Hustle!
衝刺 衝刺

563
00:35:19,980 --> 00:35:22,110
Get your asses across the damn line.
跑過終點線

564
00:35:23,410 --> 00:35:26,120
Aye, nice work, Doss.
對 幹得不錯 道斯

565
00:35:33,110 --> 00:35:34,360
This is a personal gift from
這些是美國政府

566
00:35:34,390 --> 00:35:37,060
the United States Government to each and everyone of you.
為在場各位準備的禮物

567
00:35:37,600 --> 00:35:39,650
A standard issue U.S. Rifle.
美國軍用步槍

568
00:35:39,860 --> 00:35:40,980
Caliber 30.
口徑7.62毫米

569
00:35:41,110 --> 00:35:42,020
M1
M1加蘭德步槍

570
00:35:42,270 --> 00:35:43,220
a clip-fed, shoulder-fired,
這是一款自動上膛

571
00:35:43,250 --> 00:35:45,820
semi-automatic weapon designed
半自動肩扛式武器

572
00:35:45,850 --> 00:35:49,030
to bring death and destruction to the enemy.
能夠為敵人帶去滅頂之災

573
00:35:49,390 --> 00:35:50,820
This is to be your lover,
她就是你的愛人

574
00:35:51,400 --> 00:35:52,270
your mistress,
你的心肝

575
00:35:52,710 --> 00:35:53,710
your concubine.
你的寶貝

576
00:35:54,060 --> 00:35:55,060
Perhaps,
也可以說是

577
00:35:55,250 --> 00:35:57,370
the only thing in life you'll ever truly love.
你這輩子唯一的真愛

578
00:35:58,250 --> 00:35:59,850
Fellas, let's dance.
各位 舞會開始了

579
00:36:00,230 --> 00:36:01,230
Grab a girl.
每人挑個姑娘吧

580
00:36:02,690 --> 00:36:04,480
Don't point your gun forward.
別把你們的槍朝前

581
00:36:04,500 --> 00:36:06,490
I do not want to be shot today.
我可不想今天被射中

582
00:36:06,800 --> 00:36:08,700
No matter how much you are tempted.
雖然我知道 你們很想那樣做

583
00:36:09,210 --> 00:36:11,210
Place the weapon by your side.
把槍放到你們身旁

584
00:36:13,250 --> 00:36:14,250
Pay attention.
立正

585
00:36:22,300 --> 00:36:23,930
Problem, Private Corn Stalk?
有問題嗎 玉米稈二等兵

586
00:36:23,980 --> 00:36:25,600
Is there not one in your size,
你不喜歡這槍的尺寸

587
00:36:26,070 --> 00:36:27,870
or is it the color that is the issue?
還是不喜歡這槍的顏色呢

588
00:36:27,990 --> 00:36:28,990
No, Sarge.
沒有 中士

589
00:36:31,970 --> 00:36:34,570
I was... I was told I don't have to carry a weapon.
有人跟我說 我可以不用帶武器

590
00:36:35,480 --> 00:36:36,730
Come again, step forward, Private.
再說一次 上前一步 二等兵

591
00:36:36,760 --> 00:36:38,280
I can't be hearing this right.
我剛才肯定是聽錯了

592
00:36:44,140 --> 00:36:45,740
Well, I'm sorry, Sergeant.
我很抱歉 中士

593
00:36:47,570 --> 00:36:48,900
I can't touch a gun.
我不能碰槍

594
00:36:52,310 --> 00:36:53,830
What exactly is the problem?
所以 到底出什麼問題了

595
00:36:53,850 --> 00:36:55,840
No problem, just a mistake, sir.
沒什麼問題 只是個誤會 長官

596
00:36:55,870 --> 00:36:58,230
I... I told the Army when I joined up...
我報名參軍時 已經和陸軍說過...

597
00:36:58,260 --> 00:36:59,490
That's not possible.
那不可能

598
00:37:00,130 --> 00:37:02,340
Do you know why it's not possible, Private?
你知道為什麼不可能嗎 二等兵

599
00:37:02,490 --> 00:37:03,180
No, sir.
不知道 長官

600
00:37:03,200 --> 00:37:05,690
'Cause the United States Army does not make mistakes.
因為美國陸軍是不會出錯的

601
00:37:06,230 --> 00:37:07,430
So if there's a problem,
所以 如果有問題

602
00:37:08,360 --> 00:37:10,020
you must be that problem.
那肯定就是你的問題

603
00:37:10,590 --> 00:37:13,200
I was just never supposed to be sent to a rifle company.
我本不該被編入步兵連

604
00:37:13,830 --> 00:37:15,480
He's a CO, sir.
他是個拒絕服兵役者 長官

605
00:37:20,370 --> 00:37:22,590
You're a conscientious objector,
你是個拒絕服兵役者

606
00:37:23,220 --> 00:37:25,740
- and you joined the army? - Well no, sir.
- 那你還來參軍 - 你誤會了 長官

607
00:37:26,810 --> 00:37:29,180
I'm... I'm a conscientious cooperator.
我只是堅持反對暴力而已

608
00:37:30,630 --> 00:37:32,170
Are you screwing with me, Doss?
你是在耍我嗎 道斯

609
00:37:32,190 --> 00:37:34,130
No. No, sir. I volunteered.
我沒有 長官 我是自願參軍

610
00:37:34,700 --> 00:37:37,480
I got no... no problem with wearing my uniform,
不管是穿軍服 敬禮

611
00:37:37,500 --> 00:37:39,720
or saluting the flag and... and doing my duty.
還是盡我的職責 我都沒問題

612
00:37:39,740 --> 00:37:44,050
It's just... just carrying a gun and taking a human life.
只是 持槍殺人 是絕對不行的

613
00:37:45,000 --> 00:37:47,360
You don't kill. That's all?
你不殺生 是這個意思嗎

614
00:37:47,380 --> 00:37:48,550
Yes, sir. That's all.
是的 長官 是這個意思

615
00:37:48,570 --> 00:37:51,150
You know quite a bit of killing does occur in a war.
你知道戰場上 幹的就是殺人勾當嗎

616
00:37:51,700 --> 00:37:52,240
Yes, Sir.
我知道 長官

617
00:37:52,260 --> 00:37:54,650
I mean that is the essential nature of war.
殺戮就是戰爭的本質

618
00:37:54,730 --> 00:37:55,550
Yes, sir.
是的 長官

619
00:37:55,940 --> 00:37:56,940
Alright.
好吧

620
00:37:58,010 --> 00:38:00,980
Do you have any other requirements of the United States army?
那你對美國陸軍還有什麼其他要求嗎

621
00:38:01,380 --> 00:38:03,040
Is there anything else that we can do to ensure
為了能讓您在這裏 和我們一起生活得舒心

622
00:38:03,070 --> 00:38:04,860
that you have a comfortable stay here with us?
還有什麼我們能為您做的嗎

623
00:38:04,880 --> 00:38:07,560
He doesn't wanna work on Saturday, sir.
他不想在週六執勤 長官

624
00:38:07,590 --> 00:38:10,970
Well, Saturday is... I'm a Seventh Day Adventist.
週六是... 我信奉安息日會

625
00:38:11,000 --> 00:38:14,420
So... saturday is my sabbath, so...
週六是安息日 所以

626
00:38:14,450 --> 00:38:16,170
I'm not allowed to work then.
我不能工作

627
00:38:16,200 --> 00:38:17,620
I don't think that poses a problem,
在我看來 這完全不成問題

628
00:38:17,640 --> 00:38:18,660
do you, Sergeant?
你覺得呢 中士

629
00:38:18,830 --> 00:38:21,370
We should simply ask the enemy not to invade on the Sabbath,
考慮到道斯二等兵是個虔誠的信徒

630
00:38:21,390 --> 00:38:23,240
'cause Private Doss here is a prayer.
我們應該通知敵人 讓他們別在週六發動進攻

631
00:38:24,320 --> 00:38:26,990
Alright. Now we got that clear.
好了 事情已經很清楚了

632
00:38:28,220 --> 00:38:30,310
Now let me tell you my requirements.
現在 我來跟你說說我的要求吧

633
00:38:30,430 --> 00:38:32,490
They're not as complicated as yours.
不像你的要求那麼複雜

634
00:38:32,520 --> 00:38:33,750
They are very simple.
我的要求很簡單

635
00:38:34,760 --> 00:38:37,720
As long as you're in this company under my command,
只要你還在這個軍營 只要你還是我的兵

636
00:38:37,890 --> 00:38:39,940
you will obey my orders. Period.
你就得遵守我的命令 完畢

637
00:38:41,800 --> 00:38:43,030
If you can't do it here,
如果在這裏 你都不能服從命令

638
00:38:43,050 --> 00:38:45,650
I can't trust you to do it in the battle.
那麼在戰場上 我就更不能信任你

639
00:38:50,260 --> 00:38:50,980
I'm putting you in
我會用第八條例來處理你

640
00:38:51,010 --> 00:38:53,940
for a Section 8, psychiatric discharge.
以精神問題為理由 遣送你回去

641
00:38:55,050 --> 00:38:56,050
Dismissed.
解散

642
00:38:57,060 --> 00:38:57,910
Gentlemen!
各位

643
00:38:59,040 --> 00:39:01,160
I want you to meet Private Desmond Doss.
我想向你們介紹一下 戴斯蒙德·道斯二等兵

644
00:39:01,890 --> 00:39:02,890
Apparently,
顯而易見

645
00:39:03,370 --> 00:39:05,760
Private Doss does not believe in violence.
道斯二等兵反對暴力

646
00:39:06,210 --> 00:39:07,800
He does not practice violence.
他絕不會採取暴力行動

647
00:39:08,080 --> 00:39:10,190
He will not even deign to touch a weapon.
甚至不會屈尊去碰武器

648
00:39:11,300 --> 00:39:12,700
You see, Private Doss
道斯二等兵

649
00:39:13,380 --> 00:39:15,490
is a conscientious objector.
是一位拒絕服兵役者

650
00:39:16,020 --> 00:39:17,520
So I plead with you,
在此 我請求各位

651
00:39:17,920 --> 00:39:20,710
do not look to him to save you on the battlefield,
在戰場上 就別指望他來救你們了

652
00:39:21,770 --> 00:39:23,790
because he will undoubtedly
因為他肯定會

653
00:39:24,100 --> 00:39:27,530
be too busy wrestling with his conscience to assist.
忙著和他的良心作鬥爭 根本沒時間理你們

654
00:39:27,550 --> 00:39:29,190
Sarge, that's not true, Sarge.
中士 不是這樣的 中士

655
00:39:29,210 --> 00:39:30,500
Private, as you were.
二等兵 別說話

656
00:39:34,210 --> 00:39:34,990
Now, I realize
我知道

657
00:39:35,020 --> 00:39:37,360
some of you might have strong feelings about this.
各位對這件事一定有所怨言

658
00:39:37,710 --> 00:39:39,450
It is what we men fight for.
我們浴血奮戰

659
00:39:40,170 --> 00:39:41,570
To defend our rights,
就是為了捍衛我們的權利

660
00:39:42,200 --> 00:39:43,860
and to protect our women and children.
保護我們的女人和孩子

661
00:39:45,040 --> 00:39:46,910
Even if Private Doss's belief
哪怕道斯二等兵的信仰

662
00:39:47,970 --> 00:39:50,500
might cause women and children to die.
會對婦女兒童造成傷害

663
00:39:51,180 --> 00:39:53,530
So I will expect everyone in this company
在此 我希望連隊的每一位

664
00:39:53,550 --> 00:39:57,370
to give Private Doss the full measure of respect he is due
能夠給予道斯二等兵應得的尊敬

665
00:39:58,030 --> 00:40:00,440
for the short time he will be with us.
畢竟他在這裏也待不久了

666
00:40:01,240 --> 00:40:02,430
Am I clear?
明白了嗎

667
00:40:02,780 --> 00:40:04,320
Yes, sergeant.
是 中士

668
00:40:13,470 --> 00:40:15,070
What'cha got there, Dessie?
你看什麼呢 小妹妹

669
00:40:19,130 --> 00:40:20,090
You know what that is?
你知道那是什麼嗎

670
00:40:20,110 --> 00:40:21,710
It just seems kind of small.
這個版本有點小啊

671
00:40:22,330 --> 00:40:23,920
It's half-the-Bible for half-the-man.
這本小聖經正適合你這個小男生

672
00:40:23,940 --> 00:40:25,600
For Pete's sake, Smitty give him back his Bible.
拜託 史密提 把他的聖經還他吧

673
00:40:25,620 --> 00:40:27,490
I don't remember speaking to you.
我可沒跟你說話

674
00:40:31,540 --> 00:40:32,990
So, how come you don't fight?
你為什麼不動手呢

675
00:40:33,640 --> 00:40:35,440
You think you better than us?
你是不屑跟我們動手嗎

676
00:40:36,130 --> 00:40:37,130
No.
不是

677
00:40:37,850 --> 00:40:39,300
Well, what if you're attacked?
那如果你被打了呢

678
00:40:43,060 --> 00:40:44,260
Say, like that.
例如 就像這樣

679
00:40:45,450 --> 00:40:45,760
The Bible says
聖經告訴你

680
00:40:45,790 --> 00:40:47,190
to turn your other cheekbone, don't it?
把另一側臉也湊過來 不是嗎

681
00:40:49,890 --> 00:40:52,770
See, I don't think this is a question of religion, fellas.
各位 我覺得這不是宗教信仰問題

682
00:40:53,070 --> 00:40:54,800
I think this is cowardice,
我覺得這就是懦弱

683
00:40:55,530 --> 00:40:56,660
plain and simple.
顯而易見

684
00:40:57,010 --> 00:40:58,130
You alright, Doss?
你還好嗎 道斯

685
00:40:59,300 --> 00:41:00,930
Are you chickenshit, that it?
你就是孬種 對嗎

686
00:41:02,930 --> 00:41:03,930
Go on.
來啊

687
00:41:04,800 --> 00:41:05,900
Take a poke.
打我一拳

688
00:41:07,260 --> 00:41:09,400
Tell you what, I'm gonna give a free shot.
告訴你 我讓你隨便打

689
00:41:10,010 --> 00:41:10,830
Right there.
打這裏

690
00:41:12,500 --> 00:41:13,500
Hit me, Doss.
打我啊 道斯

691
00:41:13,780 --> 00:41:14,780
Go on.
來啊

692
00:41:15,180 --> 00:41:16,050
Let him have it!
揍他

693
00:41:16,080 --> 00:41:16,940
Go ahead.
上啊

694
00:41:17,200 --> 00:41:18,060
No?
不出手嗎

695
00:41:20,800 --> 00:41:21,490
Chickenshit.
孬種

696
00:41:27,110 --> 00:41:29,010
- What is this? - Give me that.
- 這是什麼 - 還給我

697
00:41:29,040 --> 00:41:30,500
This is a fine looking broad.
這姑娘真水靈

698
00:41:30,540 --> 00:41:31,290
Nice.
真漂亮

699
00:41:31,310 --> 00:41:32,320
Hey, pass it around.
傳過來看看

700
00:41:32,820 --> 00:41:34,760
Now, this would be the kind of broad
只有真正的英雄才配得上

701
00:41:35,580 --> 00:41:37,180
that deserves a real man.
這樣的美人

702
00:41:38,540 --> 00:41:39,740
Give me that back.
把照片還給我

703
00:41:40,940 --> 00:41:41,680
Please.
求我

704
00:41:43,760 --> 00:41:44,430
Please.
求你

705
00:41:45,400 --> 00:41:47,090
"Please give it back, Smitty."
"求你 史密提 把照片還給我"

706
00:41:48,110 --> 00:41:50,110
Please give it back, Smitty.
求你 史密提 把照片還給我

707
00:42:00,410 --> 00:42:02,430
Do you hear voices, Desmond?
你有出現幻聽嗎 戴斯蒙德

708
00:42:05,610 --> 00:42:06,610
No, sir.
沒有 長官

709
00:42:07,380 --> 00:42:09,750
But I understand that God talks to you.
根據我的理解 上帝會跟你說話

710
00:42:09,780 --> 00:42:10,810
Is that right?
對嗎

711
00:42:11,020 --> 00:42:12,770
Sir, I'm not a crazy person.
長官 我並不是個瘋子

712
00:42:12,940 --> 00:42:15,640
Then how you feel... most people regard you,
那大家都認為你瘋了

713
00:42:15,670 --> 00:42:17,520
a... a crazy person?
你有什麼感受呢

714
00:42:17,540 --> 00:42:20,100
I'm... I'm different. I know that. But...
我知道我和大家不一樣 但...

715
00:42:22,550 --> 00:42:24,570
I'm not gonna pretend to be something I'm not.
我沒打算強迫自己裝得和大家一樣

716
00:42:24,600 --> 00:42:25,700
I am what I am.
我就是我

717
00:42:26,130 --> 00:42:27,240
Sounds lonely.
聽起來很孤獨啊

718
00:42:28,330 --> 00:42:29,330
Are you lonely?
你孤獨嗎

719
00:42:34,380 --> 00:42:36,050
So, you don't hear voices?
所以你沒有出現幻聽 是嗎

720
00:42:36,090 --> 00:42:37,090
No, sir.
沒有 長官

721
00:42:37,770 --> 00:42:39,010
I pray to God
我向上帝祈禱

722
00:42:39,760 --> 00:42:40,920
and I like to think He hears me,
希望他能聽見

723
00:42:40,940 --> 00:42:42,890
but it ain't a conversation,
但我並沒有和他聊天

724
00:42:43,780 --> 00:42:46,400
like the one we're pretending to have right now.
並非像我們正在假裝的這樣

725
00:42:46,740 --> 00:42:47,610
Pretending, Private?
假裝嗎 二等兵

726
00:42:47,640 --> 00:42:49,480
Well, yes, sir. I know what you really wanna do is...
是的 長官 我知道你想...

727
00:42:49,500 --> 00:42:51,650
is give me a section 8, draw me out of the Army.
想用第八條例把我趕出軍隊

728
00:42:51,680 --> 00:42:53,450
But... I'm not off...
但我沒瘋

729
00:42:53,850 --> 00:42:54,680
Up above.
我腦子沒問題

730
00:42:54,700 --> 00:42:57,050
I just simply believe what I believe.
我只是堅守我的信仰而已

731
00:42:57,080 --> 00:43:01,160
Well, I'm trying to understand, alright?
我在盡量試圖理解你 好嗎

732
00:43:01,190 --> 00:43:05,400
Was it...  Was it God who told you not to pick up a rifle?
是上帝告訴你 不要拿槍的嗎

733
00:43:05,490 --> 00:43:07,840
God says not to kill.
上帝說 不要殺戮

734
00:43:08,580 --> 00:43:10,130
That's one of His most important commandments.
那是十誡中最重要的一條

735
00:43:10,150 --> 00:43:13,770
Most people take that to mean, "Don't commit murder."
但大家都將其理解為 "不蓄意謀殺他人"

736
00:43:14,210 --> 00:43:17,260
War is completely differen set of circumstances.
戰爭 則是特殊情況

737
00:43:17,340 --> 00:43:21,050
Jesus said "A new commandment I give unto you,
主說 "我賜給你們一條新的誡律

738
00:43:22,130 --> 00:43:23,800
That you love one another,
乃是叫你們彼此相愛

739
00:43:23,830 --> 00:43:25,160
just as I have loved you."
如同我愛你一般"

740
00:43:25,180 --> 00:43:27,230
This is satan himself we're fighting.
我們面對的可是惡魔撒旦本人

741
00:43:27,250 --> 00:43:30,940
Surely, as good Christian, you can see that.
作為一名虔誠的基督教徒 你應該能明白

742
00:43:30,960 --> 00:43:34,010
I can see that, sir, and that is why I joined up.
我明白 長官 所以我才來參軍了

743
00:43:36,570 --> 00:43:38,900
But I'm sorry, I will not bear arms.
但很抱歉 我不會碰任何武器的

744
00:43:39,410 --> 00:43:42,050
His religious view is certainly unique,
毫無疑問 他的信仰非常獨特

745
00:43:42,070 --> 00:43:43,910
but they do not constitute grounds
但並不合適採用條例第八章

746
00:43:43,940 --> 00:43:45,410
for Section 8 discharge.
沒法把他趕出軍隊

747
00:43:45,920 --> 00:43:46,500
How am I supposed to
有他這樣的人

748
00:43:46,530 --> 00:43:49,010
maintain discipline with a man like that in my unit?
在我隊伍裏 我要如何才能維持秩序呢

749
00:43:49,010 --> 00:43:49,020
I don't know.
maintain discipline with a man like that in my unit?
我不知道
在我隊伍裏 我要如何才能維持秩序呢

750
00:43:49,020 --> 00:43:49,930
I don't know.
我不知道

751
00:43:50,430 --> 00:43:52,810
But he is a legitimate conscientious objector,
但他出於信仰而拒絕服兵役 是合法的

752
00:43:52,830 --> 00:43:55,010
and he must be allowed to work as combat medic,
只要能完成所有訓練內容

753
00:43:55,040 --> 00:43:58,250
provided he qualifies in all other areas in his training.
他就能以醫護兵的身份 留在軍隊裏

754
00:43:59,020 --> 00:44:02,370
Perhaps we could help make believe in his idea.
或許我們可以幫助他 改變其想法

755
00:44:03,680 --> 00:44:05,970
Yeah, you restrict him to barracks in KP.
沒錯 你讓他只負責營房和廚房的雜事

756
00:44:06,310 --> 00:44:08,870
If he throws God at you, you throw hell right at him.
他只要跟你說起上帝 你就給他點顏色看看

757
00:44:09,010 --> 00:44:10,320
I want him gone.
我要他走

758
00:44:27,440 --> 00:44:29,130
Doss, your area is in disgrace.
道斯 你的床太亂了

759
00:44:29,640 --> 00:44:30,880
It's a pig stock.
簡直就像個豬窩

760
00:44:32,060 --> 00:44:33,700
- Something funny, Ryker? - No, Sarge!
- 有什麼好笑的嗎 雷克 - 沒有 中士

761
00:44:33,720 --> 00:44:36,540
- You got some shit on your mind? - No, Sarge!
- 你腦子有毛病嗎 - 沒有 中士

762
00:44:37,870 --> 00:44:39,800
What you men fail to recognize
你們沒有意識到的

763
00:44:39,880 --> 00:44:43,670
is a unit is no better than its weakest member.
團隊中最弱者的能力 才真正決定團隊的水平

764
00:44:44,670 --> 00:44:46,420
Now, to help you learn that lesson,
為了幫助你們學習這個道理

765
00:44:46,720 --> 00:44:48,960
there will be no passes this weekend.
這個週末 所有人都不許外出

766
00:44:49,350 --> 00:44:51,130
You will all be on KP.
全都滾到廚房去幫忙

767
00:44:51,810 --> 00:44:55,200
Right now everybody on full gear for 20-mile hike.
現在 所有人全副武裝 二十英里的負重越野

768
00:44:55,430 --> 00:44:56,430
Let's go.
快點

769
00:44:56,780 --> 00:44:57,780
Let's go.
出發

770
00:45:01,780 --> 00:45:03,180
Get your heads right.
保持清醒

771
00:45:03,780 --> 00:45:06,050
Don't start feeling sorry for yourself.
不要自怨自艾

772
00:45:06,310 --> 00:45:09,130
Makes me sick seeing you feel sorry for yourself.
看到你們自怨自艾的樣子 我就覺得噁心

773
00:45:09,330 --> 00:45:11,450
You dogs don't know what tired is.
你們根本就不知道什麼是累

774
00:45:11,970 --> 00:45:14,170
We gonna keep going till I drop.
我不停下 你們都別想休息

775
00:45:16,410 --> 00:45:17,660
Come on, guys.
來吧 夥計們

776
00:45:22,570 --> 00:45:24,500
Hey, knock it off. Knock it off!
別打了 別打了

777
00:45:25,050 --> 00:45:26,450
Trying to sleep here.
我還要睡覺呢

778
00:45:29,750 --> 00:45:31,510
Get off me. Get off me.
別碰我 別碰我

779
00:45:39,170 --> 00:45:41,030
Why the hell are you still here?
你他媽到底為什麼還賴著不走呢

780
00:45:51,380 --> 00:45:53,340
- Ten-hut.- As you were.
- 立正 - 稍息

781
00:46:01,350 --> 00:46:02,350
Where's Doss?
道斯呢

782
00:46:25,640 --> 00:46:27,100
This isn't good for anybody.
這對任何人都沒有好處

783
00:46:27,380 --> 00:46:29,600
Sure ain't what I joined up for.
這確實不是我當初報名參軍的原因

784
00:46:32,110 --> 00:46:33,790
It's not about what you joined up for.
這跟你參軍的原因沒關係

785
00:46:35,170 --> 00:46:37,200
It's about the lives of every men in here.
而是關乎這裏所有人的性命

786
00:46:38,810 --> 00:46:40,210
And yours, son.
還有你的性命 小子

787
00:46:41,330 --> 00:46:42,600
It's time you quit this.
是時候退出了

788
00:46:44,240 --> 00:46:46,190
Finish getting dress and I'll walk you down.
穿好衣服 我送你出去

789
00:46:53,470 --> 00:46:54,470
It's okay, Doss.
沒事的 道斯

790
00:46:56,730 --> 00:46:57,990
There's no shame in this.
沒什麼好羞恥的

791
00:47:14,000 --> 00:47:15,000
Let's go.
走吧

792
00:47:16,180 --> 00:47:18,490
I got an extra guard duty today,
我今天還要值班

793
00:47:18,520 --> 00:47:21,440
and I'm on KP this morning, so...
早上還要去廚房幫忙 所以...

794
00:47:24,080 --> 00:47:25,080
I can't.
走不了

795
00:47:31,430 --> 00:47:32,530
Alright, Doss.
好吧 道斯

796
00:47:35,270 --> 00:47:36,350
Private Doss,
道斯二等兵

797
00:47:36,930 --> 00:47:39,410
can you identify the men that beat you?
你能認出打你的人嗎

798
00:47:46,230 --> 00:47:47,390
No, Sarge.
不 中士

799
00:47:48,050 --> 00:47:50,280
Are you saying that you don't know who attacked you?
你是說 你不知道誰打了你嗎

800
00:47:51,340 --> 00:47:53,710
I never said I was attacked, Sarge.
我沒說我被打了啊 中士

801
00:47:54,810 --> 00:47:56,940
Well, what the hell are you saying, Doss?
你到底在說什麼呢 道斯

802
00:47:57,720 --> 00:48:00,120
You bruised half your body sleeping?
你睡覺睡得遍體鱗傷的嗎

803
00:48:02,010 --> 00:48:04,330
I... I sleep pretty hard.
我睡相確實很差

804
00:48:07,930 --> 00:48:08,730
Alright.
好吧

805
00:48:09,560 --> 00:48:11,060
If you plan on getting wet this weekend,
如果這個週末 你們打算要享受艷福

806
00:48:11,090 --> 00:48:13,390
- make sure you put on a hat. - Next!
- 要記得做安全措施噢  -下一個

807
00:48:13,430 --> 00:48:15,720
I don't want anyone coming back pissing cream.
我可不想看你們帶著一身騷味回來

808
00:48:15,950 --> 00:48:18,100
What, you don't want to none for your coffee, Sarge?
難道你不想享受享受嗎 中士

809
00:48:18,450 --> 00:48:20,710
How about a shot right now, Smitty?
那現在就來一發吧 史密提

810
00:48:21,020 --> 00:48:22,790
- You speaking from experience, Sarge? - Next.
- 這是你的經驗之談嗎 中士 - 下一個

811
00:48:22,810 --> 00:48:25,020
You'd have to ask your mom about that, greaseball.
你去問問你媽就知道了 胖球

812
00:48:25,120 --> 00:48:26,550
Move!
敬禮

813
00:48:30,850 --> 00:48:31,850
At ease.
稍息

814
00:48:36,570 --> 00:48:37,780
Private Doss,
道斯二等兵

815
00:48:38,670 --> 00:48:40,710
I'm afraid I can't authorize your pass.
恐怕我不能批准你外出

816
00:48:40,740 --> 00:48:43,990
This is a furlough for men who had pass the basic training.
只有通過所有基礎訓練項目 才能享有假期

817
00:48:47,070 --> 00:48:49,650
Well, sir... respectfully, sir, I have.
恕我直言 長官 我已經通過了

818
00:48:50,990 --> 00:48:53,160
I... I put in for this furlough three weeks ago.
我三周前就開始申請這次外出了

819
00:48:53,180 --> 00:48:55,670
I'm getting married this afternoon.
今天下午 我就要結婚了

820
00:48:55,690 --> 00:48:58,850
It says you're not rifle-qualified.
上面寫著 你沒有通過步槍測試

821
00:48:59,720 --> 00:49:01,560
Well, I'm not required to carry a rifle, sir.
但我不需要佩槍 長官

822
00:49:01,590 --> 00:49:02,820
Colonel... Colonel Stelzer he...
上校... 施特爾策上校 他...

823
00:49:02,850 --> 00:49:05,460
Colonel Stelzer's determination was...
施特爾策上校的規矩是說

824
00:49:05,870 --> 00:49:08,520
"Doss must be allowed to work as a combat medic,
"如果道斯想要留在軍隊 做醫護兵

825
00:49:08,650 --> 00:49:13,090
provided he qualifies in all other areas of his training."
他必須通過所有的訓練測試"

826
00:49:13,350 --> 00:49:16,310
And you have not qualifiedon the rifle range, private.
但你並沒有通過步槍訓練 二等兵

827
00:49:17,120 --> 00:49:18,120
Pretty clear.
非常清楚

828
00:49:21,340 --> 00:49:23,940
Show me you know how to handle a rifle,
讓我看看 你會不會拿槍

829
00:49:24,190 --> 00:49:25,930
and I'll sign your furlough.
如果你會 我就批准你外出

830
00:49:26,560 --> 00:49:28,320
- Corporal Cannon. - Sir.
- 坎農下士 - 長官

831
00:49:28,340 --> 00:49:30,930
Hand private Doss your firearm.
把你的佩槍遞給道斯二等兵

832
00:49:40,130 --> 00:49:41,270
I won't touch a rifle, sir.
我不會碰槍的 長官

833
00:49:41,300 --> 00:49:43,540
I'm not asking you, Private.
我沒有在詢問你的意見 二等兵

834
00:49:44,310 --> 00:49:47,150
That is a direct order from a company commander.
這是指揮官給你下達的直接指令

835
00:49:47,830 --> 00:49:49,830
For God's sake, Doss,
看在上帝的份上 道斯

836
00:49:51,010 --> 00:49:53,440
you stop this nonsense and quit.
別胡鬧了 退出吧

837
00:49:54,420 --> 00:49:55,560
Refuse,
如果你拒絕

838
00:49:56,150 --> 00:49:59,100
and I will have no recourse but to court martial you,
那我就只能把你送上軍事法庭了

839
00:49:59,510 --> 00:50:00,680
and you will spend
在整個戰爭期間

840
00:50:00,710 --> 00:50:03,600
the duration of the war in a military prison.
你都將只能待在軍事監獄裏

841
00:50:05,690 --> 00:50:06,980
I can't, sir.
我做不到 長官

842
00:50:19,390 --> 00:50:22,140
How much longer would you like to wait, Dorothy?
你還想等多久 多蘿西

843
00:50:23,540 --> 00:50:25,540
I think it's been long enough.
我想 我們已經等得夠久了

844
00:50:26,960 --> 00:50:28,270
I'm so very sorry.
很抱歉

845
00:50:28,960 --> 00:50:31,450
Sometimes men just get cold feet.
有時候男人就會臨陣退縮

846
00:50:33,490 --> 00:50:34,860
Some men might.
有些男人可能會吧

847
00:50:36,020 --> 00:50:37,600
Not my Desmond.
但我的戴斯蒙德不會

848
00:51:10,410 --> 00:51:12,700
You probably think I'm a really son of a bitch
你可能認為 我就是個混蛋

849
00:51:13,360 --> 00:51:15,930
who cares only about regulations and not his men.
只在乎規定 而不愛惜自己手下

850
00:51:19,440 --> 00:51:20,440
May I?
我可以看一下嗎

851
00:51:27,310 --> 00:51:29,730
I believe in this book as much as any men.
我和其他人一樣 也對聖經深信不疑

852
00:51:30,310 --> 00:51:31,550
And just like any man,
也和其他人一樣

853
00:51:31,690 --> 00:51:32,830
I wrestled with my conscience,
良心備受煎熬

854
00:51:32,850 --> 00:51:33,720
but what do you do
但當這世上你所珍視的一切

855
00:51:33,740 --> 00:51:36,650
when everything you value in this world is under attacked?
都受到攻擊時 你該怎麼辦

856
00:51:37,880 --> 00:51:39,080
I don't know, sir.
我不知道 長官

857
00:51:40,870 --> 00:51:43,540
I ain't got answers to questions that big,
我不能回答如此深刻的問題

858
00:51:44,300 --> 00:51:47,500
but I also feel like my values are under attack,
但我也感覺到 我的價值觀正受到衝擊

859
00:51:48,100 --> 00:51:49,520
and I don't know why.
我甚至都不知道為什麼

860
00:51:49,870 --> 00:51:50,820
I don't give a rat-ass
我可不在乎你那什麼鬼原則

861
00:51:50,850 --> 00:51:53,170
about your principles because the Japs don't.
因為日本人也不會在乎

862
00:51:53,810 --> 00:51:55,180
If one of them attacks you
如果敵人襲擊你

863
00:51:55,210 --> 00:51:57,320
and some wounded soldier, what are you gonna do?
和其他受傷的士兵 你該怎麼辦

864
00:51:57,890 --> 00:51:59,490
Hit him with your Bible?
用聖經打他嗎

865
00:52:00,230 --> 00:52:02,250
I'm prepared to give my life for my men.
我願意為我的隊友 獻出生命

866
00:52:02,560 --> 00:52:05,100
You don't win wars by giving up your life.
光靠犧牲自己的生命 並不能贏得戰爭

867
00:52:06,190 --> 00:52:06,950
Look.
聽著

868
00:52:07,490 --> 00:52:08,210
I'm only here because
我來這裏

869
00:52:08,240 --> 00:52:10,520
I don't wanna see you rotting in a prison cell.
是因為 我不想看到你被困在監獄裏

870
00:52:11,070 --> 00:52:12,070
Plead guilty,
認罪吧

871
00:52:12,220 --> 00:52:13,780
throw yourself at the mercy of the court.
在法庭上 請求他們的寬恕

872
00:52:13,810 --> 00:52:15,820
Maybe they'll let you go home and pray.
或許他們會讓你安然無恙地回家

873
00:52:18,530 --> 00:52:21,100
Let the brave men out there go and win this war.
讓那些勇敢的人 去贏得這場戰爭吧

874
00:52:30,010 --> 00:52:32,540
If I can't convinceyou, maybe she can.
如果我說服不了你 或許她可以

875
00:52:34,630 --> 00:52:36,630
They wouldn't let me call you.
他們不讓我打電話給你

876
00:52:38,480 --> 00:52:40,410
I knew it wasn't your making.
我就知道這不是你的錯

877
00:52:43,820 --> 00:52:45,360
What've they done to you?
他們對你幹了什麼

878
00:52:48,100 --> 00:52:49,320
It's okay. I'm alright.
沒事 我沒事

879
00:52:49,350 --> 00:52:51,970
I just went a couple of rounds with the wall and lost.
我只是跟牆打了幾個回合 然後輸了而已

880
00:52:53,000 --> 00:52:55,450
They're saying you could go to prison, Desmond.
他們說你很可能被送進監獄 戴斯蒙德

881
00:52:56,460 --> 00:52:57,640
Leavenworth.
利文沃斯堡監獄

882
00:52:58,490 --> 00:53:00,160
There must be some other way.
肯定還有其他辦法

883
00:53:00,510 --> 00:53:02,150
I don't know what that could be.
我不知道還能怎麼辦

884
00:53:02,450 --> 00:53:03,780
I've done everything they asked me
除了碰槍這件事

885
00:53:03,800 --> 00:53:04,760
except this one thing,
他們說的我全照做了

886
00:53:04,790 --> 00:53:05,970
and I'm being treated like a criminal
就因為我不肯殺人

887
00:53:05,990 --> 00:53:07,240
just 'cause I won't kill.
他們就如同對待犯人般對待我

888
00:53:07,270 --> 00:53:08,270
You tried.
你盡力了

889
00:53:08,830 --> 00:53:10,560
Nobody can say you didn't.
沒人能否認這一點

890
00:53:11,560 --> 00:53:13,760
But who are you gonna save in prison?
但你在監獄裏 能救到誰呢

891
00:53:16,020 --> 00:53:16,800
Probably nobody.
估計誰也救不了吧

892
00:53:16,820 --> 00:53:18,440
Then why can't you just pick up the stupid gun
那你為什麼 就不能拿起那該死的槍

893
00:53:18,470 --> 00:53:19,590
and wave it around.
隨便裝裝樣子呢

894
00:53:19,860 --> 00:53:22,400
You don't have to use it, just meet them halfway.
你不需要用它 只要做出讓步就好了

895
00:53:24,320 --> 00:53:25,390
But I can't do that.
但我做不到

896
00:53:25,410 --> 00:53:26,690
Yes, you can. It's just pride.
你可以的 你只是太驕傲了

897
00:53:26,750 --> 00:53:27,630
Pride and stuborness.
驕傲又頑固

898
00:53:27,650 --> 00:53:30,000
Don't confuse your will with the Lord's.
不要混淆你的意志和主的意志

899
00:53:43,080 --> 00:53:44,350
Have I been prideful?
我很驕傲嗎

900
00:53:46,560 --> 00:53:48,180
Maybe I am prideful.
或許我確實很驕傲

901
00:53:52,830 --> 00:53:54,720
But I don't know how I'm going to live with myself
但如果不堅持我自己的信仰

902
00:53:54,740 --> 00:53:57,030
if I don't stay true to what I believe.
我都不知道 該怎樣生活下去

903
00:53:58,170 --> 00:54:00,690
much less how you could live with me.
更重要的是 該怎樣和你一起生活

904
00:54:02,400 --> 00:54:05,560
I'd never be the man that I want to be in your eyes.
我永遠不會成為 你眼中真正的男人

905
00:54:12,480 --> 00:54:14,080
I fell in love with you
我之所以愛你

906
00:54:14,910 --> 00:54:17,370
because you weren't like anyone else.
因為你跟其他人不一樣

907
00:54:18,920 --> 00:54:20,590
and you didn't try to be.
而你也不曾改變自己

908
00:54:23,150 --> 00:54:27,610
Do not think for one moment that you'll disappoint me.
永遠不要覺得 你會讓我失望

909
00:54:30,480 --> 00:54:31,950
I will love you,
無論怎樣

910
00:54:32,630 --> 00:54:34,140
no matter what.
我都愛你

911
00:54:46,460 --> 00:54:48,360
I don't know what he's gonna do.
我不知道他要怎麼辦

912
00:54:48,890 --> 00:54:50,660
He loses no matter what.
不管怎樣 他都會輸

913
00:54:51,560 --> 00:54:52,660
They want him to plead guilty
他們想要他認罪

914
00:54:52,690 --> 00:54:54,940
but then he'll get dishonorable discharge...
但這樣他就會被開除軍籍...

915
00:54:55,510 --> 00:54:58,350
Otherwise he fights them, he for sure goes to prison.
或者拒不認罪 那他肯定會進監獄的

916
00:54:59,210 --> 00:55:00,590
Either way, they'll call him a coward
不管怎樣 他都會被人們稱作懦夫

917
00:55:00,610 --> 00:55:02,430
and I don't see how he can live with that.
我不知道他怎麼能那樣活下去

918
00:55:03,750 --> 00:55:05,930
Well, thank you, Dorothy.
謝謝 多蘿西

919
00:55:06,930 --> 00:55:08,660
If you get to talk to him,
如果你有機會跟他說話

920
00:55:09,550 --> 00:55:10,590
tell him that we love him
告訴他 我們愛他

921
00:55:10,610 --> 00:55:11,880
and that  we're praying for him.
我們為他禱告

922
00:55:11,900 --> 00:55:13,090
We're praying for both of you.
為你們倆祈禱

923
00:55:13,960 --> 00:55:14,960
I will.
我會的

924
00:55:15,550 --> 00:55:16,550
Bye-bye.
再見

925
00:55:25,290 --> 00:55:26,890
Will you leave me alone?
你能不要煩我嗎

926
00:55:27,240 --> 00:55:29,130
Will you just go?
你能走開嗎

927
00:55:29,270 --> 00:55:31,170
Tom, you're out of your mind, you're delirious...
湯姆 你已經瘋了 簡直不可理喻...

928
00:55:31,200 --> 00:55:32,860
Of course I'm out of my mind.
我當然是瘋了

929
00:55:32,890 --> 00:55:35,390
What do you think I am? I'm out of my mind.
不然呢 我已經瘋了

930
00:55:35,660 --> 00:55:37,680
Will you leave this room? Stupid woman!
你給我滾出這間房 蠢女人

931
00:55:37,900 --> 00:55:39,320
God! Put it down!
天哪 把槍放下

932
00:55:39,350 --> 00:55:41,020
Get away from me, woman.
死女人 離我遠點

933
00:55:58,910 --> 00:56:00,110
I got that, sir.
明白了 先生

934
00:56:12,020 --> 00:56:13,180
May I help you, sir?
我有什麼能幫您嗎 先生

935
00:56:13,270 --> 00:56:16,150
I wish to speak to Brigadier General Musgrove.
我想跟斯格羅夫准將說幾句話

936
00:56:16,230 --> 00:56:17,370
Not without an appointment you can't.
沒有預約 是不行的

937
00:56:17,390 --> 00:56:18,810
That would be quite impossible.
那是不可能的

938
00:56:25,710 --> 00:56:27,340
If you would kindly tell him
能請你轉告他

939
00:56:27,360 --> 00:56:30,850
Corporal Thomas Doss would appreciate a brief word.
托馬斯·道斯下士想跟他說幾句話嗎

940
00:56:31,540 --> 00:56:33,600
He is in a very important meeting.
他在參加一個很重要的會議

941
00:56:34,580 --> 00:56:37,220
I fought with him in France at Belleau Wood.
在法國貝洛森林戰役中 我曾與他並肩作戰

942
00:56:37,250 --> 00:56:38,880
He was my Captain.
當時 他是我的上尉

943
00:56:41,210 --> 00:56:44,680
Please ma'am. It's... It's most vital.
求你了 女士 我有很重要的事

944
00:56:48,230 --> 00:56:49,550
Thank you, ma'am.
謝謝你 女士

945
00:56:54,250 --> 00:56:56,870
There's a man out there, Thomas Doss, wants to see you.
外面有位叫做托馬斯·道斯的人想要見您

946
00:56:56,890 --> 00:56:57,750
Doss?
道斯

947
00:57:02,430 --> 00:57:03,730
Be over in a minute.
很快就能結束

948
00:57:03,740 --> 00:57:05,170
You'll be home safe and sound,
你很快就能安全回家了

949
00:57:05,200 --> 00:57:07,300
like nothing ever happened.
就像什麼都沒發生過一樣

950
00:57:12,600 --> 00:57:13,600
I love you.
我愛你

951
00:58:00,650 --> 00:58:02,780
This is a hearing into the matter of Private Desmond Doss.
本次聽證會 被告為戴斯蒙德·道斯二等兵

952
00:58:02,800 --> 00:58:04,390
The charge is disobeying
其罪名為

953
00:58:04,420 --> 00:58:06,890
a series of direct orders from his commanding officer.
不服從指揮官的多項指令

954
00:58:06,910 --> 00:58:08,530
How says the defendant?
被告方做何辯護

955
00:58:09,840 --> 00:58:13,540
Private Doss wishes to enter a "not guilty" plea.
道斯二等兵 希望做無罪辯護

956
00:58:14,780 --> 00:58:16,680
Is that so, Private? I thought this was agreed.
是嗎 二等兵 我本以為已經談妥了

957
00:58:16,700 --> 00:58:19,360
You wanted to enter some sort of plea bargain.
你打算認罪 達成協議

958
00:58:21,120 --> 00:58:23,530
- Yes, sir. But I changed my mind.- Just like that?
- 是的 長官 但我改變主意了 - 就這樣嗎

959
00:58:23,540 --> 00:58:25,940
You wish to proceed to a court-martial.
你想繼續在軍事法庭上辯護嗎

960
00:58:27,070 --> 00:58:28,070
Yes, sir.
是的 長官

961
00:58:28,590 --> 00:58:30,660
Well, on your head, then. Private.
那後果自負 二等兵

962
00:58:31,800 --> 00:58:32,800
Proceed.
請繼續

963
00:58:36,030 --> 00:58:36,890
Your honor,
法官大人

964
00:58:37,410 --> 00:58:38,710
Private Doss
道斯二等兵

965
00:58:38,850 --> 00:58:40,450
waves his morality at us,
到處炫耀他的道德觀

966
00:58:40,480 --> 00:58:42,400
like it's some kind of badge of honor.
就像炫耀榮譽勳章

967
00:58:42,460 --> 00:58:43,990
He flaunts his contempt
通過違抗

968
00:58:44,020 --> 00:58:45,110
by directly disobeying
直屬指揮官的一系列指令

969
00:58:45,110 --> 00:58:47,390
a series of direct orders from his commanding officer.
來顯示自己的輕蔑之情

970
00:58:47,520 --> 00:58:49,020
When the very best of our young men
與此同時 我們國家最出色的年輕人們

971
00:58:49,040 --> 00:58:51,290
are sacrificing their lives against...
正在戰場上 不惜生命 抗擊...

972
00:58:54,270 --> 00:58:55,660
- You okay? - Yes.
- 你還好吧 - 還好

973
00:58:56,790 --> 00:58:59,130
- Are they still deliberating? - Yes, sir.
- 還在審議嗎 - 是的

974
00:58:59,320 --> 00:59:01,350
Okay, now you go take this in there.
好吧 你把這個拿進去

975
00:59:01,370 --> 00:59:03,640
I can't. It's strictly military personnel.
不行 非軍事人員不得入內

976
00:59:04,210 --> 00:59:05,680
Well, then you get one of them to take it in.
那你要他們中一個拿進去吧

977
00:59:05,710 --> 00:59:08,080
They ain't out to help. They're fixing to burying him.
他們不會幫忙的 他們都恨不能把他埋了

978
00:59:08,270 --> 00:59:09,610
There's only one question
軍事法庭只需詢問被告

979
00:59:09,640 --> 00:59:12,250
that any military court need ask of the accused.
一個簡單問題就可以了

980
00:59:12,730 --> 00:59:16,440
Do you deny disobeying Colonel Sangston's direct orders?
你要否認 自己曾違抗塞恩斯頓上校的直接命令嗎

981
00:59:19,160 --> 00:59:20,990
Well, do you, Private?
你否認嗎 二等兵

982
00:59:26,830 --> 00:59:27,950
No, sir. I don't.
不 長官 我不否認

983
00:59:27,970 --> 00:59:29,700
Why are you contesting it, then?
那你到底在爭論什麼

984
00:59:29,830 --> 00:59:32,500
Why is it so important to you, given your refusal to even
你既然拒絕觸碰武器 那到底為什麼

985
00:59:32,530 --> 00:59:34,950
touch a weapon to serve in a combat unit?
要加入戰鬥分隊呢

986
00:59:35,900 --> 00:59:38,260
Because when the Japanese attacked Pearl Harbor,
因為在日本人襲擊珍珠港後

987
00:59:38,290 --> 00:59:39,890
I took it personal.
我也感同身受

988
00:59:41,260 --> 00:59:43,530
Everyone I knew was on fire to join up,
我認識的每個人 都熱血沸騰地想參軍

989
00:59:43,560 --> 00:59:44,730
including me.
其中也包括我

990
00:59:47,700 --> 00:59:49,680
There were two men in my hometown,
在我的家鄉 有兩個人

991
00:59:51,550 --> 00:59:52,820
declared 4-F unfit,
因為體檢不合格

992
00:59:52,840 --> 00:59:55,220
they killed themselves 'cause they couldn't serve.
沒能入伍 而選擇了自殺

993
00:59:59,400 --> 01:00:01,140
I had a job in a defense plant,
之前 我在兵工廠工作

994
01:00:01,170 --> 01:00:03,710
and I could've taken a deferment, but that ain't right.
本來可以申請延期服役 但那是不對的

995
01:00:06,400 --> 01:00:10,190
It isn't right that other men should fight and die,
當其他人都在戰場上 浴血奮戰時

996
01:00:11,020 --> 01:00:13,070
that I would just be sitting at home safe.
我卻在家高枕無憂 這樣是不對

997
01:00:13,140 --> 01:00:14,440
I need to serve.
我要報效祖國

998
01:00:16,450 --> 01:00:19,450
I got the energy and the passion to serve as a medic,
我有熱情也有能力 成為一名醫護兵

999
01:00:21,350 --> 01:00:23,610
right in the middle with the other guys, no less danger,
與其他人並肩戰鬥 同甘共苦

1000
01:00:23,640 --> 01:00:24,320
just...
只是...

1001
01:00:26,030 --> 01:00:27,570
while everybody else is taking life,
當其他人都在奪取生命時

1002
01:00:27,600 --> 01:00:29,070
I'm going to be saving it.
我將會拯救生命

1003
01:00:32,590 --> 01:00:35,040
With the world so set on tearing itself apart,
世界已經開始分崩離析

1004
01:00:35,070 --> 01:00:36,890
it doesn't seem like such a bad thing to me
而有人想要盡力 維持一點點原樣

1005
01:00:36,910 --> 01:00:39,270
to want to put a little bit of it back together.
在我看來 這似乎並不是壞事

1006
01:00:42,910 --> 01:00:44,400
- Sorry, sir, nobody is allowed to... - No,
- 抱歉 先生 任何人禁止入內 - 不

1007
01:00:44,430 --> 01:00:46,580
You don't understand. My son is the defendant.
你不明白 我的兒子是被告

1008
01:00:46,670 --> 01:00:47,570
I understand, sir.
我明白 先生

1009
01:00:47,590 --> 01:00:48,180
But nobody is allowed...
但任何人禁止入內

1010
01:00:48,210 --> 01:00:49,840
I have information, that's important.
我有重要的消息

1011
01:00:49,860 --> 01:00:50,630
Sir, you are not allowed...
先生 你不能...

1012
01:00:50,660 --> 01:00:52,760
While the sentiments expressed are laudable,
雖然你表達的精神值得讚賞

1013
01:00:52,790 --> 01:00:55,790
the facts of the charge seem incontestable, so...
然而被控的罪行 卻是無可爭辯 所以...

1014
01:00:56,870 --> 01:00:59,130
What the hell is going on out there?
外面發生什麼事了

1015
01:00:59,740 --> 01:01:01,010
- Sir. - Let him go.
- 先生 - 讓他進來吧

1016
01:01:12,310 --> 01:01:13,910
That's a Great War uniform.
那是一戰的制服

1017
01:01:13,930 --> 01:01:15,160
It is, sir.
是的 長官

1018
01:01:15,660 --> 01:01:17,420
Sir, I need to show you this.
長官 我想讓您看看這個

1019
01:01:17,450 --> 01:01:18,720
With respect, sir,
我沒有冒犯的意思 先生

1020
01:01:18,780 --> 01:01:21,010
you are no longer a member of the military.
但您已經不再是軍人了

1021
01:01:21,030 --> 01:01:23,390
You're unable to attend this hearing. I'm sorry.
您不能參加這次聽證會 我很抱歉

1022
01:01:23,930 --> 01:01:26,110
Is that truly the way it works, sir?
現在軍隊真的是這樣了嗎 長官

1023
01:01:26,980 --> 01:01:28,360
You fight for your country,
你為國家而戰

1024
01:01:28,390 --> 01:01:30,320
you lose so much that were dear to you,
失去了許多寶貴的東西

1025
01:01:30,350 --> 01:01:31,760
and then you're done with?
然後你卻一文不值嗎

1026
01:01:32,120 --> 01:01:34,920
The uniform's forgotten. You have no voice?
軍裝被遺忘 老兵被漠視

1027
01:01:35,340 --> 01:01:36,530
You were at Lyons?
您參加了里昂戰役嗎

1028
01:01:36,660 --> 01:01:38,700
I was, sir. And at Belleau Wood.
是的 長官 以及貝洛森林戰役

1029
01:01:38,880 --> 01:01:41,410
Twice decorated. I see it, sir.
兩次都被授予了勳章 我看到了 先生

1030
01:01:42,340 --> 01:01:44,840
I take it you're the Private's father.
我想您是這位二等兵的父親

1031
01:01:44,870 --> 01:01:46,880
I am, sir. Thomas Doss.
沒錯 長官 我是托馬斯·道斯

1032
01:01:46,910 --> 01:01:48,470
Then, as former military man,
那麼作為一名退役軍人

1033
01:01:48,500 --> 01:01:50,040
you know there are laws here.
您應該知道這裏的法律

1034
01:01:50,070 --> 01:01:51,050
Sir, I know the law.
長官 我知道那些法律

1035
01:01:51,080 --> 01:01:53,400
and I know my son is protected by those laws.
我也知道 法律會維護我兒子應該有的權利

1036
01:01:53,420 --> 01:01:55,510
They are framed in our constitution.
這些都是被憲法所保障的

1037
01:01:55,920 --> 01:01:57,580
And I believe in them, as he does.
我相信這些法律 他也一樣

1038
01:01:58,030 --> 01:02:00,500
They are why I went and fought to protect them.
正是為了捍衛我們的法律 我才會去報名參軍

1039
01:02:01,580 --> 01:02:03,490
At least that's what I thought I was doing
至少當初我奔赴戰場時 我是這樣想的

1040
01:02:03,510 --> 01:02:04,810
because if it wasn't for that
因為 如果不是那樣

1041
01:02:04,830 --> 01:02:07,870
then I have no idea what the hell I was doing there, sir.
那我就不知道我為何而戰 長官

1042
01:02:09,750 --> 01:02:11,630
Thank you, Corporal Doss.
謝謝您 道斯下士

1043
01:02:14,020 --> 01:02:15,550
Let me have the letter.
把信交給我吧

1044
01:02:23,320 --> 01:02:24,320
You must go.
您必須離開

1045
01:02:40,290 --> 01:02:41,570
"The defendant's rights as a
"國會法案保護

1046
01:02:41,600 --> 01:02:44,650
conscientious objector are protected by an Act of Congress."
被告所擁有 出於信仰拒絕服兵役的權利"

1047
01:02:44,680 --> 01:02:47,910
"And he cannot be compelled to waive those rights.
"並且不能強迫他放棄這些權利

1048
01:02:48,830 --> 01:02:50,090
That includes in this case
包括本案中

1049
01:02:50,120 --> 01:02:52,870
his disobeying orders to bear arms."
他擁有的違反軍令拒絕拿起武器的權利"

1050
01:02:53,130 --> 01:02:55,020
Signed, Bridgadier General Musgrove,
簽名 斯格羅夫准將

1051
01:02:55,050 --> 01:02:57,490
War Services Commander, Washington, D.C.
華盛頓特區 作戰指揮部

1052
01:02:58,010 --> 01:02:58,780
Colonel?
上校

1053
01:03:03,350 --> 01:03:05,470
I withdraw the charges, sir.
我撤回指控 長官

1054
01:03:05,590 --> 01:03:07,450
Then this case is dismissed.
那麼案件審理結束

1055
01:03:08,060 --> 01:03:10,800
Private Doss, you are free to run into the hell fire of
道斯二等兵 你被允許 可以手無寸鐵

1056
01:03:10,830 --> 01:03:13,960
battle without a single weapon to protect yourself.
衝進硝煙瀰漫的戰場了

1057
01:03:15,190 --> 01:03:16,990
You may resume your duties
你將重拾責任

1058
01:03:17,240 --> 01:03:19,120
and begin training as a combat medic.
受訓成為一名醫護兵

1059
01:03:25,390 --> 01:03:26,790
- Where is he? - Gone.
- 他在哪兒 - 走了

1060
01:03:26,810 --> 01:03:28,520
Straight after. I begged him to stay.
他出來就直接離開了 我求過他留下來

1061
01:03:28,550 --> 01:03:30,610
- I told him you'd want to see him. - No, I understand.
- 我告訴過他 你肯定想見他 - 我明白

1062
01:03:31,840 --> 01:03:33,770
When you get home, you tell him I love him.
等你回家了 告訴他 我愛他

1063
01:03:33,810 --> 01:03:35,970
Okay. Okay.
好的 好的

1064
01:04:15,370 --> 01:04:17,810
You better come home to me.
你一定要回家 回我身邊

1065
01:04:30,000 --> 01:04:33,100
Uncle Sam is smiling. Peaceful as a child
# 山姆大叔微微笑 平靜似小孩 #

1066
01:04:33,430 --> 01:04:34,860
But never get him rowdy.
# 但千萬不要把他惹惱 #

1067
01:04:34,880 --> 01:04:36,190
Cut it out, Hollywood.
別唱了 大明星

1068
01:04:36,220 --> 01:04:36,810
Shut up.
閉嘴吧

1069
01:04:36,840 --> 01:04:38,410
- So now you wanna play? - C'mon pipe down.
- 現在你想玩了嗎 - 拜託 別唱了

1070
01:04:38,440 --> 01:04:39,960
- Shut up, man. - Shut up.
- 閉嘴吧  夥計 - 閉嘴

1071
01:04:39,990 --> 01:04:42,000
I swear to God, Hollywood, I'll shoot you.
我發誓 大明星 我要斃了你

1072
01:04:42,020 --> 01:04:42,820
Put a sock in it, will you?
用襪子堵上嘴 可以嗎

