01:58:21,690 --> 01:58:22,490
We got him.
我們接住他了

1637
01:58:22,980 --> 01:58:24,380
It's good. It's good.
沒事了 沒事了

1638
01:58:32,080 --> 01:58:34,370
Woah. It's okay. It's okay. Doss.
沒事了 沒事了 道斯

1639
01:58:35,140 --> 01:58:36,730
Come on, Doss. You're safe.
沒事了 道斯 你安全了

1640
01:58:37,540 --> 01:58:39,580
- Okay. - Come on, Doss. Come on.
- 好 - 過來吧 道斯

1641
01:58:54,760 --> 01:58:58,950
- Desmond, it's alright. - It's alright.
- 戴斯蒙德 沒事了 - 沒事了

1642
01:58:59,020 --> 01:59:00,020
Desmond.
戴斯蒙德

1643
01:59:03,180 --> 01:59:04,550
- Easy. - Easy. Easy.
- 小心 - 小心 小心

1644
01:59:04,580 --> 01:59:05,580
Here. Come on.
坐吧 坐這裏

1645
01:59:06,060 --> 01:59:07,060
Take a seat.
快坐下

1646
01:59:11,220 --> 01:59:12,290
Are you wounded?
你受傷了嗎

1647
01:59:17,200 --> 01:59:17,880
No.
沒有

1648
01:59:18,440 --> 01:59:19,440
No.
沒有

1649
01:59:21,740 --> 01:59:24,470
Let's get this soldier to a hospital tent, right now.
快把這位士兵送到醫療帳篷

1650
01:59:24,630 --> 01:59:25,760
Come on. Easy now.
來吧 慢慢來

1651
01:59:26,210 --> 01:59:27,770
Easy. Easy. Make some space.
小心一點 大家讓讓

1652
02:00:11,500 --> 02:00:13,550
We need someone to come and clean up in here.
我們需要有人來幫忙 清理下這裏

1653
02:00:16,140 --> 02:00:17,140
Where's Irv?
爾文在哪裏呢

1654
02:00:17,310 --> 02:00:18,010
Irv?
爾文

1655
02:00:18,350 --> 02:00:20,070
You mean Schecter, the Medic?
你是說塞克特 那個醫護兵嗎

1656
02:00:20,270 --> 02:00:21,530
He didn't make it.
他沒挺過來

1657
02:00:21,930 --> 02:00:22,870
He died of shock.
死於休克

1658
02:00:22,900 --> 02:00:23,900
No plasma.
沒有血漿了

1659
02:00:25,400 --> 02:00:26,000
I'm sorry.
很遺憾

1660
02:01:02,150 --> 02:01:03,880
All I saw was a skinny kid.
我一直以為 你只是個瘦弱的孩子

1661
02:01:04,090 --> 02:01:05,890
I didn't know who you were.
我根本不瞭解你的為人

1662
02:01:10,280 --> 02:01:11,540
You've done more than any other man
你對這個國家所做出的貢獻

1663
02:01:11,560 --> 02:01:13,800
could've done in the service of his country.
超過了其他任何服役的軍人

1664
02:01:14,660 --> 02:01:17,270
And I have never been more wrong about someone in my life.
我這輩子 從來沒有如此誤解過別人

1665
02:01:18,850 --> 02:01:21,050
I hope one day you could forgive me.
我希望有朝一日 你能原諒我

1666
02:01:33,640 --> 02:01:35,700
We have to go back up tomorrow.
明天我們要繼續攻打鋼鋸嶺

1667
02:01:38,350 --> 02:01:41,220
I realize that tomorrow is your Sabbath.
我知道 明天是你的安息日

1668
02:01:47,230 --> 02:01:49,790
Most of these men don't believe the same way you do.
他們很多人都不像你這樣 擁有虔誠的信仰

1669
02:01:51,770 --> 02:01:53,390
But they believe so much
但他們堅信

1670
02:01:54,300 --> 02:01:56,110
in how much you believe.
你對自己信仰的虔誠

1671
02:01:58,960 --> 02:02:00,140
What you did on that Ridge
你在鋼鋸嶺上的所作所為

1672
02:02:00,170 --> 02:02:01,630
is just nothing short of a miracle,
簡直堪稱奇跡

1673
02:02:02,030 --> 02:02:03,560
and they want a piece of it.
他們也希望能享有這份奇跡

1674
02:02:06,730 --> 02:02:09,000
And they're not gonna go up there without you.
如果你不去 他們是不會上去的

1675
02:02:20,090 --> 02:02:21,370
What the hell is your delay, Captain?
上尉 你們為什麼還沒行動

1676
02:02:21,400 --> 02:02:23,750
You were supposed to begin that assault 10 minutes ago.
十分鐘前 你們就該發動攻擊了

1677
02:02:23,970 --> 02:02:25,180
We're waiting, sir.
我們還在等待 長官

1678
02:02:25,210 --> 02:02:26,470
Waiting for what?
等什麼

1679
02:02:29,190 --> 02:02:32,050
For Private Doss to finish praying for us, sir.
等待道斯二等兵 為我們祈禱完畢 長官

1680
02:02:32,100 --> 02:02:33,700
Private Doss is praying for you?
道斯二等兵正在為你們祈禱

1681
02:02:33,730 --> 02:02:35,760
Who the hell is Private Doss?
他媽的誰是道斯二等兵

1682
02:02:57,640 --> 02:02:58,770
Let's go to work.
準備出發

1683
02:04:51,690 --> 02:04:52,560
Down!
跪下

1684
02:04:52,580 --> 02:04:55,810
Get down! Get down on the ground!
跪下 跪在地上

1685
02:04:55,830 --> 02:04:57,560
On the ground. Now!
立刻跪下

1686
02:05:36,970 --> 02:05:39,490
Lay down! Lay down! Lay down! I got the morphine.
躺下 快躺下 我有嗎啡

1687
02:05:40,860 --> 02:05:42,720
Let's go! Let's go. Let's get this man outta here.
快走 快走 快帶他離開這裏

1688
02:05:42,740 --> 02:05:43,740
Go! Go!
快 快

1689
02:05:48,410 --> 02:05:49,410
My Bible...
我的《聖經》

1690
02:05:49,830 --> 02:05:52,420
My Bible. My Bible...
我的《聖經》 我的《聖經》

1691
02:05:52,450 --> 02:05:54,960
Stop! Stop! Stop! Stop! Stop!
停 停 快停下

1692
02:05:55,140 --> 02:05:58,790
My Bible. My Bible.
我的《聖經》 我的《聖經》

1693
02:05:59,360 --> 02:06:00,360
Okay.
知道了

1694
02:07:15,940 --> 02:07:17,480
You going home, Desmond.
戴斯蒙德 你馬上就能回家了

1695
02:07:17,930 --> 02:07:19,530
We've taken the Hacksaw.
我們拿下了鋼鋸嶺

1696
02:07:23,870 --> 02:07:26,160
Hold up! Hold up! Desmond.
等等 等等 戴斯蒙德

1697
02:07:28,310 --> 02:07:29,310
Desmond.
戴斯蒙德

1698
02:09:16,360 --> 02:09:18,820
I was praying the whole time.
當時 我一直在祈禱

1699
02:09:19,600 --> 02:09:20,790
I just kept praying,
我一直向主祈禱

1700
02:09:20,810 --> 02:09:23,820
"Lord, please help me get one more."
"主啊 求求你 讓我再救一個吧"

1701
02:09:24,840 --> 02:09:25,720
When I got this,
每當救下一個人之後

1702
02:09:25,750 --> 02:09:29,440
I said "Lord, please help me get one more".
我就繼續祈禱 "主啊 求你 讓我再救一個吧"

1703
02:09:35,990 --> 02:09:37,810
I would say anyone is wrong
在我看來

1704
02:09:37,830 --> 02:09:40,090
to try to compromise somebody's conviction.
試圖改變任何人的信仰 都是不明智的

1705
02:09:40,110 --> 02:09:43,210
I don't care whether it's the army or what it is.
不論是在軍隊 還是在其他地方

1706
02:09:43,720 --> 02:09:45,530
When you're on a conviction,
只要你秉承自己的信仰

1707
02:09:46,230 --> 02:09:47,490
that is not a joke.
那就絕不是玩笑

1708
02:09:49,570 --> 02:09:50,900
That's what you are.
而是真正的你

1709
02:09:52,660 --> 02:09:54,130
Even though I said those things
雖然我對他說了許多

1710
02:09:54,150 --> 02:09:56,410
to him in regard to carrying a rifle,
說他應該拿槍上戰場

1711
02:09:56,710 --> 02:09:58,730
then... then he would never be my...
如果他不拿槍

1712
02:09:58,760 --> 02:10:02,650
by my damn side at all unless he had a rifle.
我就絕不會和他一起並肩作戰

1713
02:10:03,120 --> 02:10:05,600
But then, in the long run,
但最終

1714
02:10:05,860 --> 02:10:10,170
finding out that he was one of the bravest persons alive.
我卻發現 他是最英勇的士兵之一

1715
02:10:10,820 --> 02:10:12,280
And then to have him ended up
而最後 還需要他來救我

1716
02:10:12,300 --> 02:10:16,330
saving my life was the irony of the whole thing.
這簡直太諷刺了

1717
02:10:16,790 --> 02:10:21,230
Blood had ran down through to the fella's face and eyes.
鮮血從他的臉龐和眼睛上流下

1718
02:10:22,250 --> 02:10:25,900
He was laying there just groaning and calling for a medic.
當時 他躺在那裏 呻吟著 不停地叫醫護兵

1719
02:10:27,560 --> 02:10:31,450
I took the water from my canteen and got some bandages,
我從水壺中倒了些水 拿了些紗布

1720
02:10:31,650 --> 02:10:33,890
and I washed his face.
幫他洗了臉

1721
02:10:34,760 --> 02:10:36,510
And when I was washing his eyes,
當他眼裏的鮮血 被擦乾淨之後

1722
02:10:36,980 --> 02:10:39,310
his eyes came up.
他睜開了眼睛

1723
02:10:39,330 --> 02:10:42,500
Man, he just lit up.
他簡直高興壞了

1724
02:10:44,170 --> 02:10:47,050
He says "I thought I was blind."
他說 "我還以為我瞎了"

1725
02:10:48,410 --> 02:10:51,220
And if I hadn't got anything more out of the war
而當時他臉上的笑容

1726
02:10:51,240 --> 02:10:53,310
than that smile he gave me,
對我而言

1727
02:10:53,490 --> 02:10:56,580
I wouldn't have been well repaid.
就是最好的回報

